The current-carrying capacity of cables between the battery system and PCE shall be â€”
(a) in accordance with AS/NZS 3008.1.1;
(b) not less than the maximum continuous current of the battery system;
(c) not less than the maximum continuous current of the PCE; and
(d) not less than the rating of the overcurrent protection device.
NOTE The current-carrying capacity of cables should be selected to ensure efficient operation of the system and to minimize voltage drop.
